1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:04,280
Imagine you're a chef in one of the busiest restaurant kitchens in the city.

2

00:00:04,280  -->  00:00:07,980
You have an order for your signature dish and you could make

3

00:00:07,980  -->  00:00:13,200
each component from scratch every time an order comes in from a hungry customer.

4

00:00:13,200  -->  00:00:15,140
But that would be exhausting,

5

00:00:15,140  -->  00:00:17,365
tedious, and time consuming.

6

00:00:17,365  -->  00:00:22,515
You think to yourself, there has to be a better way to do this.

7

00:00:22,515  -->  00:00:26,790
Instead, you've carefully prepped ingredients and created

8

00:00:26,790  -->  00:00:31,890
steps that you could repeat for each dish ensuring consistency and speed.

9

00:00:31,890  -->  00:00:36,890
In fact, your steps are so well defined and repeatable that you started to allow

10

00:00:36,890  -->  00:00:39,870
other staff members to cook the special dish

11

00:00:39,870  -->  00:00:43,750
following the recipe because everything is all accounted for.

12

00:00:43,750  -->  00:00:45,870
It works like clockwork.

13

00:00:45,870  -->  00:00:50,090
In Python, functions are like these prepped steps.

14

00:00:50,090  -->  00:00:53,150
They allow us to break down our code into

15

00:00:53,150  -->  00:00:58,070
smaller repeatable recipes that we can call on anytime we need them.

16

00:00:58,070  -->  00:01:01,610
Instead of writing the same code over and over again,

17

00:01:01,610  -->  00:01:07,245
we can create a function once and use it whenever and wherever we want.

18

00:01:07,245  -->  00:01:10,950
This not only makes our programming more efficient,

19

00:01:10,950  -->  00:01:14,240
but also keeps our code organized and easy to manage.

20

00:01:14,240  -->  00:01:19,850
Anyone could run the prepared steps and get the same output each time.

21

00:01:19,850  -->  00:01:23,350
In this section, we'll explore the basics of functions,

22

00:01:23,350  -->  00:01:26,690
seeing how they can transform our coding process just as

23

00:01:26,690  -->  00:01:31,850
a chef's prep work transforms the process of cooking in a busy kitchen.
